definitions.definition: Synonym of foraminifer ( “ any of a large group of aquatic amoeboid protists of the subphylum Foraminifera , characterized by streaming granular ectoplasm that among other things is used for catching food , often with a calcareous shell with many holes through which pseudopodia protrude ” ) . [from mid 19th c.]
